x^p + y^p = p^z
 \frac{x^p + y^p}{x + y} = \sum_{i=0}^{p-1}x^{(p-1)-i}(-y)^i \implies (x+y) |p^z \implies x + y = p^n, \text{ }n < z   
p =2
 p=3, x = 3^n, y = 2\cdot3^n, z = 2 + 3n 
